        </section>

        <!-- Right: selected thread preview / reply box -->
        <aside class="discussion-detail">
            <header class="detail-header">
                <h2 class="detail-title">Thread preview</h2>
                <p class="detail-subtitle">
                    Select a discussion from the center list to view the conversation.
                </p>
            </header>

            <!-- Example static thread content -->
            <div class="detail-thread">
                <h3 class="detail-thread-title">Need help with Calculus homework</h3>
                <p class="detail-thread-meta">Started by Alex J · Calculus I</p>

                <div class="detail-messages">
                    <div class="message">
                        <div class="message-header">
                            <span class="message-author">Alex J</span>
                            <span class="message-time">Today 2:14 PM</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="message-body">
                            I am having trouble with limits and derivatives. I understand the rules, but I do not see
                            why they work. Any explanations or example problems would be appreciated.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="message">
                        <div class="message-header">
                            <span class="message-author">Jordan L</span>
                            <span class="message-time">Today 2:28 PM</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="message-body">
                            One way to think about derivatives is to treat them as the rate of change at a single point.
                            You can try graphing the function and drawing tangent lines to see how the slope changes.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="message">
                        <div class="message-header">
                            <span class="message-author">Tutor Morgan</span>
                            <span class="message-time">Today 2:45 PM</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="message-body">
                            If you share a specific problem, we can walk through it and connect the formal rules to the
                            geometric picture. Limits help define the slope very precisely, especially at corners or
                            points where the function changes quickly.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="detail-reply">
                <label for="reply-text" class="reply-label">Add a reply</label>
                <textarea
                    id="reply-text"
                    class="reply-textarea"
                    placeholder="Write your message here"
                ></textarea>
                <div class="reply-actions">
                    <button class="primary-btn" type="button">Post Reply</button>
                    <button class="secondary-btn" type="button">Save Draft</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </aside>
    </main>

